{"aid": "40077993", "title": "Visualise Urbanisation in Africa", "url": "https://africapolis.org/en", "domain": "africapolis.org", "votes": 1, "user": "atlasunshrugged", "posted_at": "2024-04-18 16:33:24", "comments": 0, "source_title": "Africapolis", "source_text": "Africapolis\n\n  * Home\n  * Maps and analysis\n  * Research\n  * Data\n  * About\n\n# Visualise urbanisation in Africa\n\n#### Africapolis is a research and data visualisation tool used to map,\nanalyse and understand urbanisation and urban growth in Africa\n\n#### Explore\n\nExplore data for more than 9,200 urban agglomerations in 54 African countries.\n\n#### Country reports\n\nA look into the urbanisation dynamics of 54 countries since 1950 and how they\nare shaping new urban realities.\n\n#### Data\n\nBuild custom data visualisations on urbanisation in Africa and download the\ndata.\n\n### Newsletter\n\nSubscribe to our newsletter!\n\nSubscribe\n\n#### April Newsletter (01)\n\nWelcome to Africapolis: Our First Newsletter\n\n#### May Newsletter (02)\n\nLaunch conference - 2023 revision and update\n\n#### Conference Agenda - 21 June 2023\n\nLaunch of the Africapolis 2023 Revision and Update\n\n#### June Newsletter (03)\n\nJune Special Edition - Upcoming 2023 Africapolis data release\n\n#### July Newsletter (04)\n\nRecap of the 2023 Africapolis launch event\n\n### What is Africapolis\n\n#### Mapping a new urban reality.\n\nIn 2015, more than 50% of Africans lived in urban agglomerations. Cities,\nurban planning and management are key to delivering on the SDGs and a New\nUrban Agenda. Africapolis data and evidence supports cities and governments to\nmake urban areas more inclusive, productive and sustainable.\n\n#### A new approach to defining urban.\n\nStarting from the ground up Africapolis adopts a systematic and consistent\ndefinition of urban. By combining demographic sources, satellite and aerial\nimagery, Africapolis enables comparative and long-term analyses of urban\ndynamics. It covers all 9,200 urban agglomerations with more than 10,000\ninhabitants in 54 African countries.\n\n#### Understanding what drives urbanisation in Africa today.\n\nAfrica has the fastest urban growth in the world. By 2050, Africa's urban\nareas will be home to an additional 950 million people. Capturing how this\ngrowth is changing the size, structure and functional features of urban\nnetworks is key for managing and planning future trends.\n\n#### There are only few big cities but many small ones.\n\nIn Africa, as elsewhere, there are only few big cities but many small ones.\nThe continent has 11 urban areas with more than five million inhabitants and\nmore than 7,500 secondary cities with fewer than 500,000 inhabitants. Yet,\nmany of these urban agglomerations are absent from most international\ndatabases.\n\n### Data driven stories\n\n#### Urban agglomeration network\n\nA total of 320,162 pairings are made by connecting all urban agglomerations\nthat are 120 kilometres or less from one another.\n\n#### Cross-border agglomerations in Africa\n\nMore than 42 million people (almost 8% of total urban population) of the\ncontinent live in these 645 cross-border cities.\n\n#### Top 50 largest agglomerations in Africa\n\nOne of the main drivers of urban growth in Africa is the expansion of built-up\nareas.\n\n### Key reports\n\nAfrica's Urbanisation Dynamics 2022Africa's Urbanisation Dynamics 2020\n\n### Video\n\n### In the media\n\nLes Echos, Urbanisation africaine : une opportunit\u00e9 \u00e9conomique encore mal exploit\u00e9e, 06/28/2023Fratmat.info (C\u00f4te d'Ivoire), Urbanisation : 279 agglom\u00e9rations cr\u00e9\u00e9es dans l'espace Uemoa entre 2015 et 2020 selon lOcde, 06/22/2023Osservatore Romano.va, \u201cAfrica123\u201d guardando al futuro, 06/16/2023Focus.de, \u201eSie sind Klimarisiken st\u00e4rker ausgesetzt\u201cWie die Urbanisierung Afrika \u00fcberrollt, 05/19/2023DW, Africa Drives Global Urbanization, 05/17/2023Xataca, Nigeria ser\u00e1 el tercer pa\u00eds m\u0